items.name: Device contact details
items.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.  If no contact information is known, the value is the zero-length string.

items.name: Device description
items.description: A textual description of the entity.  This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software.

items.name: Device location
items.description: The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor').  If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

items.name: Device name
items.description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name.  If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

items.name: Device uptime
items.description: The time since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.

item_prototypes.name: Utilization of processor #$1
item_prototypes.description: The average, over the last minute, of the percentage of time that this processor was not idle. Implementations may approximate this one minute smoothing period if necessary.

discovery_rules.name: Disk partitions
discovery_rules.description:
The rule will discover all disk partitions matching the global regexp "Storage devices for SNMP discovery".

{$SNMP_COMMUNITY} is a global macro.

item_prototypes.name: Allocation units for storage $1
item_prototypes.description: The size, in bytes, of the data objects allocated from this pool.  If this entry is monitoring sectors, blocks, buffers, or packets, for example, this number will commonly be greater than one.  Otherwise this number will typically be one.

item_prototypes.name: Description of storage $1
item_prototypes.description: A description of the type and instance of the storage described by this entry.

item_prototypes.name: Total disk space on $1
item_prototypes.description: This is a calculated item, we need it to get total disk space in bytes.

item_prototypes.name: Total disk space on $1 in units
item_prototypes.description: The size of the storage represented by this entry, in units of hrStorageAllocationUnits. This object is writable to allow remote configuration of the size of the storage area in those cases where such an operation makes sense and is possible on the underlying system. For example, the amount of main memory allocated to a buffer pool might be modified or the amount of disk space allocated to virtual memory might be modified.

item_prototypes.name: Used disk space on $1
item_prototypes.description: This is a calculated item, we need it to get used disk space in bytes.

item_prototypes.name: Used disk space on $1 in units
item_prototypes.description: The amount of the storage represented by this entry that is allocated, in units of hrStorageAllocationUnits.

trigger_prototypes.name: Free disk space is less than 15% on volume {#SNMPVALUE}
